dataIdInfo.idAbs: This line data layer represents roads for Oneida County, Wisconsin in 2018. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Oneida_Roads_2018.gdb.[The roads feature class contains information regarding centerlines of public and private roads in the county. The roads contain geocoding information as well as the road name. Some road centerlines have been GPS'd to insure their accuracy while others were digitized from aerial photography. State and Federal highways are included in this dataset, while some counties choose to digitize or represent divided highways this is not the case in this dataset.]
dataIdInfo.idPurp: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. [Graphically represent the approximate centerline of the traveled roadways within the county.]
